School officials were notified today by District Health Department 4 that another health department notified them of a possible COVID-19 exposure in our area. Attendees at Wednesday's, Tawas vs. Alpena soccer game in the Alpena High School stadium grandstands from 7-9 p.m. should monitor for symptoms of the coronavirus.

If they do not develop symptoms within 14 days of these dates, there is nothing to be done. Those that develop symptoms within 14 days of these dates should contact their doctor and consider COVID-19 testing.

Signage at our stadium clearly states that spectators shall sit 6 feet apart at all athletic contests. Additionally, student athletes were not in direct contact with spectators in the grandstands.

APS Families: We are not currently charging student's for breakfast or lunch. USDA has expanded the Summer Food Program Waiver, allowing schools to offer a Free Breakfast and Free Lunch. The extension will last through December 31st, 2020 – OR until funding runs out. Parents should still fill out a Free or Reduced application for 20-21 in order to qualify once this funding runs out. Families with students at ACES, HINKS, LINCOLN, or SANBORN will be asked to fill out a Household Survey instead, as Free and Reduced applications are not needed for these schools.

Info regarding meals for online learners is coming soon.

We want to welcome our students back to school. We anticipate many students will transported by parents, and want to make this process as simple as possible. post_text:
APS Safe Return to School
Many families witnessed the enhanced safety precautions for kids returning to school this week at open houses and other welcome events. For our families and community that haven’t been to a building in person, we want you to understand some of the physical changes you will see in our buildings.
Limitations on visitors in the buildings and visitors must complete a Covid-19 screening to enter
Enhanced signage to help remind students about the importance of hygiene and maintaining spacing to keep us safe
Repurposed spaces used to decrease crowding
Access to masks at the available doorways for those that need them
Increased access to hand washing and hand sanitizer
Limits on the sizes of any groups in the same space
We will focus all our efforts on operating in a manner that maintains the safety of our students and staff and allows us to continue to deliver in person instruction.

Boys & Girls Club of Alpena
September 1 at 3:45 PM ·

The Club now has open enrollment for our after school programming.
To have your child participate in after school programming, please visit our website at bgcalpena.org and fill out the online membership form. If you are planning to have your child bused from their school please fill out the APS transportation request which can be found on the APS website.
The Club will be opening for school year programming Tuesday, September 8th. The school year hours of operation will be Monday thru Friday from 2 p.m. - 6 p.m. The Club will be offering a daily dinner at 4:30 p.m. The cost of membership for the school year is $10 per child. The Club will re-evaluate the potential of an online homework help and different hours of operation after the first week of school.
*** Parents who had their child attend during the summer do not have to fill out the school year form, but please check your email for the school year updates and short survey.
Any questions please call 356-0214.

ParentVUE Grade and Attendance Notifications (Smartphone APP available!)
You can set up your account in ParentVUE to get notified if grades fall below a certain percentage or when the student has been late or missed a class.
1. Parents need to go into "My Account", check the box for the features they want to activate, such as grades or attendance.
2. click Update Account.
3. This will then bring up another screen for them to choose the options of what day of the week, what percentage to send the notice, etc.

APS Elementary Online Course Registration/Chromebook Distribution

If you are a parent/guardian of an Alpena Public Schools elementary student and you have registered for APS Online for a learn at home experience this fall, please stop by Alpena High School on Wednesday, August 26, 2020, anytime between 5:30 PM - 7:00 PM. Short informational sessions will be held continuously during those times in the AHS Auditorium. A parent/guardian will fill out APS required paperwork and Elementary building principals will be on hand for questions and will hand out chromebooks. Face masks and social distancing is required and we ask only one parent (no children) to attend.

A parent/guardian will fill out APS required paperwork and Elementary building principals will be on hand for questions and will hand out chromebooks. Face masks and social distancing is required and we ask only one parent (no children) to attend.

School Messenger Automated Calling System
Requests for removal can be made to any school building, to the main switchboard (358-5200), or by using the “Press 5” function and confirming by pressing 1 at the start of any call.
Families can manage their own contact information by removing or adding information using Synergy ParentVue which is available at alpenaschools.com.
Families can use the free School Messenger Info center App for IOS or Android to control their own contact preferences or review missed messages.
There is also a web portal https://infocenter.schoolmessenger.com/#/home where they can do the same. You must have an email address in your Synergy account to use the mobile apps or web portal.

Alpena Early College
June 1 at 3:01 PM ·

Early College Candidates for Cohort 7 (finishing 10th Grade now), interviews will begin on Friday June 5th. There will be daytime, evening and weekend times available to accommodate all family schedules. If you are not comfortable meeting in person we will schedule an online meeting. Call Mr. Fitzpatrick to arrange a time to meet 989 464 6447. The student and at least one parent/guardian are required to attend. Please read and understand these rules. They are for your safety and my own. Interviews rules will be as follows:

1. They will take place in the AHS library

2. Exterior doors as well as library doors will be open

3. Applicant and a parent or parents only (At least one parent/guardian is required)

4. Masks required

5. Interview stations will be set up to maintain 6 feet of spacing

6. Interview stations will be rotated after each interview so they can be sanitized. (Maximum 8 interviews daily)

7. Waiting families must remain in cars until the previous applicant family leaves

School Messenger Automated Calling System
Requests for removal can be made to any school building, to the main switchboard (358-5200), or by using the “Press 5” function and confirming by pressing 1 at the start of any call.
Families can manage their own contact information by removing or adding information using Synergy ParentVue which is available at alpenaschools.com.
Families can use the free School Messenger Info center App for IOS or Android to control their own contact preferences or review missed messages.
There is also a web portal https://infocenter.schoolmessenger.com/#/home where they can do the same. You must have an email address in your Synergy account to use the mobile apps or web portal.

Decision Day is inspired by the NCAA's National Signing Day to reinforce that excellence in the classroom should be given as much pomp and circumstance as excellence as an athlete. College Decision Day is Michigan's adoption of National College Signing Day. We salute all our seniors and look forward to them pursuing their goals in education and careers.
Click on the link and hit the present button toward the top right to watch the slide show.
https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1xodbt9C8NCG10x1AeP7AW_NdBpC7fACZMhr6Ou6VuX8/edit?usp=sharing

post_text:
End of the School Year at Alpena Public Schools
Grades JK-2nd Teachers will post a final choice board for students for the final two weeks
Grades 3rd-5th Teachers will continue with Google Classroom
Grades 6th-12th should submit all assignments by 5/27

May 28th and 29th Instructional staff will have virtual office hours and use Google Classroom in the morning and have state mandated professional development in the afternoon.
June 1st-3rd State mandated professional development days for staff.
June 4th will be the final day of this unprecedented school year.
6th-12th teachers will offer office hours to support students with any final questions.
K-5th students will have their last Google Meet that day.

School Messenger Automated Calling System
Requests for removal can be made to any school building, to the main switchboard (358-5200), or by using the “Press 5” function and confirming by pressing 1 at the start of any call.
Families can manage their own contact information by removing or adding information using Synergy ParentVue which is available at alpenaschools.com.
Families can use the free School Messenger Info center App for IOS or Android to control their own contact preferences or review missed messages.
There is also a web portal https://infocenter.schoolmessenger.com/#/home where they can do the same. You must have an email address in your Synergy account to use the mobile apps or web portal.

Early College applicants, I'm very excited to get to know you all and I hope you are doing your best through this challenging time. We will have a new early college group next year and I still plan to do interviews when circumstances will allow them to be held. I'm not certain yet when that will be. If it becomes necessary we will conduct them by phone or online but I prefer to do them in person and will wait for now to see when that may be possible. If you have questions please feel free to reach out to me by email fitzpatrickl@alpenaschools.com or phone 358 5043 or message me through the Early College Facebook page.

Michigan Attorney General Dana Nessel issued a consumer alert to ensure Michiganders who are now unemployed due to COVID-19 and qualify for the Federal Communications Commission’s (FCC) Lifeline program are aware of a newly simplified application process.

The Lifeline program is in place to provide low-income subscribers with a discount on monthly telephone, broadband internet, or voice-broadband bundled services purchased from participating providers.

https://www.michigan.gov/ag/0,4534,7-359-81903_20942-528854--,00.html

shared_text:
Feed the Need - Alpena
May 9 at 3:31 PM ·

With heavy hearts we announce we will not be hosting our free food distribution on Friday, May 15th. Due to circumstances out of our control, we have to find a new location for our free pop-up pantry. Please know our team is working hard to secure a new location with the goal of hosting our next distribution on Friday, May 22nd. We will announce details here as soon as they are confirmed.

We will miss seeing our guests next week! We appreciate the stories you share with our team when we see you every Friday. So, until we meet again, can you do us a favor and send us a message sharing how Feed the Need - Alpena distributions have helped you during these difficult times? We will never share your name or personal details.

We would like to thank the Boys & Girls Club of Alpena for everything they have done to support our team these past few months.

To our neighbors, our guests, our family and friends... we WILL see you soon!

During this unprecedented school closure, many families have requested quality educational resources for their children while they are away from school. APS has compiled a number of resources to help keep students' minds engaged and learning during this crisis. Visit our For Students page to review and access these resources.

Families can manage their own contact information by removing or adding information using Synergy ParentVue which is available at alpenaschools.com.
Families can use the free School Messenger Info center App for IOS or Android to control their own contact preferences or review missed messages.
There is also a web portal https://infocenter.schoolmessenger.com/#/home where they can do the same. You must have an email address in your Synergy account to use the mobile apps or web portal.

post_text:
School Messenger Automated Calling System
Requests for removal can be made to any school building, to the main switchboard (358-5200), or by using the “Press 5” function and confirming by pressing 1 at the start of any call.
Families can manage their own contact information by removing or adding information using Synergy ParentVue which is available at alpenaschools.com.
Families can use the free School Messenger Info center App for IOS or Android to control their own contact preferences or review missed messages.
There is also a web portal https://infocenter.schoolmessenger.com/#/home where they can do the same. You must have an email address in your Synergy account to use the mobile apps or web portal.

Dual Enrolled and Early College students, we are hoping you have made a successful transition to learning online in your ACC courses.
Parents, please sit with your student and have them login to their blackboard account so you can see how they are doing. We do not have the ability to see their grades at ACC.
Students should be communicating with their ACC instructors daily by email.
Students that need help with ACC technology can call 358 7374 or email helpdesk@alpenacc.edu.
Students that need a device to access the internet for school please email Mr. Berriman berrimant@alpenaschools.com to arrange to borrow a chrome book.
ACC is still offering tutoring by phone or video. You can contact the student success center at 358 7270 or dietza@alpenacc.edu to arrange tutoring.

shared_text:
Alpena Community College
March 26 at 3:59 PM ·

With the health and safety of students, employees, and the public as its top priority, Alpena Community College has decided to postpone its 2020 Commencement ceremony and related end-of-the-year activities until further notice. Originally scheduled for May 7, 2020, Commencement will be rescheduled later in the year.

Even though ACC has postponed the Commencement ceremony, eligible students who have submitted a graduation application will still graduate. ACC Registrar Sheila Rupp will complete graduation audits after Spring 2020 Semester grades are posted to verify completion of requirements and degrees/certificates will be awarded to all eligible graduates. Questions regarding graduation status may be directed to the Registrar’s Office (rupps@alpenacc.edu, 989-358-7353).

Alpena County George N. Fletcher Public Library
March 26 at 11:47 AM ·

Stuck without a library card? Alpena Public Library now offers online library card sign-ups and renewals!

Cards will be issued for six months and allow access Alpena County Library's online resources, including access to ebooks, audiobooks, movies, and more!

Please note that card sign-ups and renewals will be processed on weekdays from 10:00am - 3:00pm. Your patience is appreciated! Residents outside of Alpena County are asked to contact their local library for information about library cards and online resources.

Apply for a card today at www.alpenalibrary.org!

Alpena Public Schools added 10 new photos.
March 17 at 3:46 PM ·

What a day!! Every single unit of our organization played their part to take on the humbling task of feeding our kids - bus drivers, food service, maintenance, instructional assistants, secretaries, teachers, administrators - WE ALL MADE THIS HAPPEN!!! We distributed 729 bags of food which equates to 2,916 meals to our kids today. We got to work together in a way we never have before and I know that we have a new appreciation for each other as a result.

ParentVUE Grade and Attendance Notifications (Smartphone APP available!)
You can set up your account in ParentVUE to get notified if grades fall below a certain percentage or when the student has been late or missed a class.
1. Parents need to go into "My Account", check the box for the features they want to activate, such as grades or attendance.
2. click Update Account.
3. This will then bring up another screen for them to choose the options of what day of the week, what percentage to send the notice, etc.

2. click Update Account.
3. This will then bring up another screen for them to choose the options of what day of the week, what percentage to send the notice, etc.
